{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015smp5HmwchVxFUog2SYvGU","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Specification: [300] Referral System\n     2→\n     3→## Meta\n     4→\n     5→| Field | Value |\n     6→|-------|-------|\n     7→| Status | Ready |\n     8→| Priority | P1 |\n     9→| Track | Extended |\n    10→| NR_OF_TRIES | 0 |\n    11→\n    12→---\n    13→\n    14→## Overview\n    15→\n    16→A Hyperliquid-style referral system where any player can generate a unique referral code, share it, and earn a perpetual share of the platform fee from every game their referred players complete. Referred players receive a benefit for joining via a referral link (see FR-3 for options). The system is entirely off-chain for v1 — no program changes required.\n    17→\n    18→## User Stories\n    19→\n    20→- As a player, I want to generate a referral link so that I can invite friends and earn passive rewards from their gameplay\n    21→- As a new player, I want to use a referral code so that I receive a signup benefit (fee rebate or bonus reward)\n    22→- As a referrer, I want to see how many players I've referred and how much I've earned so that I can track my referral performance\n    23→- As a referrer, I want to claim my accumulated earnings so that I receive SOL in my wallet\n    24→- As an operator, I want to set custom referral rates for KOL wallets so that partnership agreements are honored\n    25→\n    26→---\n    27→\n    28→## Capability Alignment\n    29→\n    30→- **`docs/SCOPE.md` references**: Section 2 \"Not Implemented in Current Baseline\" → \"Referral and creator monetization systems\"\n    31→- **Current baseline fit**: Not Implemented\n    32→- **Planning bucket**: Extended\n    33→\n    34→## Required Context Files\n    35→\n    36→- `docs/DECISIONS.md` — fee structure (500 bps flat fee, single treasury via PlatformConfig)\n    37→- `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/` — frontend entrypoint\n    38→- `sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/` — on-chain fee constants (for reference, not modified)\n    39→- Backend settlement logic (settlement worker, DB schema)\n    40→\n    41→## Contract Files\n    42→\n    43→- No existing mocks — this is a new system\n    44→- API contract defined in FR-7 below\n    45→\n    46→---\n    47→\n    48→## System Invariants (v1)\n    49→\n    50→These invariants are non-negotiable for correctness and abuse resistance:\n    51→\n    52→1. **Single referrer binding:** each referee wallet can be linked to only one referrer wallet for life (unless operator manually unlinks via admin tooling outside v1 scope).\n    53→2. **No self-referral:** `referrer_wallet !== referee_wallet` enforced at API + DB layers.\n    54→3. **Lamports-only accounting:** all stored/transported monetary values use integer lamports (`BIGINT` in DB, string in JSON APIs).\n    55→4. **Atomic settlement + earning write:** referral earning insert must be in the same DB transaction as game settlement write.\n    56→5. **Idempotent async handlers:** referral queue handlers must use domain keys (`claim_id`, `round_id + referee_wallet`, etc.), never `event_queue.id`, for de-duplication.\n    57→6. **Exactly-once effect in practice:** queue may deliver at-least-once; side-effects must remain safe under replays.\n    58→7. **No on-chain protocol changes:** v1 referral economics remain off-chain and treasury-operated.\n    59→\n    60→---\n    61→\n    62→## Functional Requirements\n    63→\n    64→### FR-1: Referral Code Generation\n    65→\n    66→Any player with a connected wallet can generate a referral code. No eligibility gate — open from day one.\n    67→\n    68→**Rationale:** The sybil incentive is negligible (max benefit from self-referral is 50 bps of wagered amount = referrer fee share, and self-referral is blocked on-chain). An eligibility gate hurts organic growth more than it prevents abuse.\n    69→\n    70→**Code format:**\n    71→- Auto-generated: 8-character alphanumeric (`a-z2-9`, excluding ambiguous `0/O/1/l`)\n    72→- Optional custom code: 3-16 characters, alphanumeric + hyphens, must be unique\n    73→- URL format: `taunt.bet/r/{CODE}`\n    74→\n    75→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n    76→- [ ] Authenticated player can generate a referral code via API\n    77→- [ ] Code is 8-char alphanumeric by default, collision-checked with retry\n    78→- [ ] Player can optionally set a custom code (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`, unique)\n    79→- [ ] Each player has exactly one active code (generating a new one replaces the old one)\n    80→- [ ] Code is persisted in `referral_codes` table\n    81→\n    82→### FR-2: Referral Linking\n    83→\n    84→When a player signs up or connects their wallet via a referral link (`taunt.bet/r/CODE`), they are permanently linked to the referrer. Alternatively, a player can manually enter a referral code in their settings.\n    85→\n    86→**Rules:**\n    87→- One referrer per player, immutable once set\n    88→- First code applied wins — cannot change referrer\n    89→- Self-referral blocked (same wallet cannot be both referrer and referee)\n    90→\n    91→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n    92→- [ ] Visiting `taunt.bet/r/{CODE}` stores the code (localStorage) until the player authenticates\n    93→- [ ] On authentication, if the player has no referrer and a stored/submitted code exists, the link is created\n    94→- [ ] Player can manually enter a referral code via API (settings page)\n    95→- [ ] Attempting to change an existing referrer returns an error\n    96→- [ ] Self-referral (referrer wallet = referee wallet) is rejected\n    97→- [ ] Referral link is stored in `referral_links` table with `created_at` timestamp\n    98→\n    99→### FR-3: Referee Fee Rebate\n   100→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"22eabd0a-3a3b-489d-bc57-d8e8d222d116","uuid":"ae7705f0-c73c-49b1-8e4e-5649c5a9084b","timestamp":"2026-03-24T21:23:16.639Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/300-referral-system/spec.md","content":"# Specification: [300] Referral System\n\n## Meta\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| Status | Ready |\n| Priority | P1 |\n| Track | Extended |\n| NR_OF_TRIES | 0 |\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nA Hyperliquid-style referral system where any player can generate a unique referral code, share it, and earn a perpetual share of the platform fee from every game their referred players complete. Referred players receive a benefit for joining via a referral link (see FR-3 for options). The system is entirely off-chain for v1 — no program changes required.\n\n## User Stories\n\n- As a player, I want to generate a referral link so that I can invite friends and earn passive rewards from their gameplay\n- As a new player, I want to use a referral code so that I receive a signup benefit (fee rebate or bonus reward)\n- As a referrer, I want to see how many players I've referred and how much I've earned so that I can track my referral performance\n- As a referrer, I want to claim my accumulated earnings so that I receive SOL in my wallet\n- As an operator, I want to set custom referral rates for KOL wallets so that partnership agreements are honored\n\n---\n\n## Capability Alignment\n\n- **`docs/SCOPE.md` references**: Section 2 \"Not Implemented in Current Baseline\" → \"Referral and creator monetization systems\"\n- **Current baseline fit**: Not Implemented\n- **Planning bucket**: Extended\n\n## Required Context Files\n\n- `docs/DECISIONS.md` — fee structure (500 bps flat fee, single treasury via PlatformConfig)\n- `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/` — frontend entrypoint\n- `sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/` — on-chain fee constants (for reference, not modified)\n- Backend settlement logic (settlement worker, DB schema)\n\n## Contract Files\n\n- No existing mocks — this is a new system\n- API contract defined in FR-7 below\n\n---\n\n## System Invariants (v1)\n\nThese invariants are non-negotiable for correctness and abuse resistance:\n\n1. **Single referrer binding:** each referee wallet can be linked to only one referrer wallet for life (unless operator manually unlinks via admin tooling outside v1 scope).\n2. **No self-referral:** `referrer_wallet !== referee_wallet` enforced at API + DB layers.\n3. **Lamports-only accounting:** all stored/transported monetary values use integer lamports (`BIGINT` in DB, string in JSON APIs).\n4. **Atomic settlement + earning write:** referral earning insert must be in the same DB transaction as game settlement write.\n5. **Idempotent async handlers:** referral queue handlers must use domain keys (`claim_id`, `round_id + referee_wallet`, etc.), never `event_queue.id`, for de-duplication.\n6. **Exactly-once effect in practice:** queue may deliver at-least-once; side-effects must remain safe under replays.\n7. **No on-chain protocol changes:** v1 referral economics remain off-chain and treasury-operated.\n\n---\n\n## Functional Requirements\n\n### FR-1: Referral Code Generation\n\nAny player with a connected wallet can generate a referral code. No eligibility gate — open from day one.\n\n**Rationale:** The sybil incentive is negligible (max benefit from self-referral is 50 bps of wagered amount = referrer fee share, and self-referral is blocked on-chain). An eligibility gate hurts organic growth more than it prevents abuse.\n\n**Code format:**\n- Auto-generated: 8-character alphanumeric (`a-z2-9`, excluding ambiguous `0/O/1/l`)\n- Optional custom code: 3-16 characters, alphanumeric + hyphens, must be unique\n- URL format: `taunt.bet/r/{CODE}`\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Authenticated player can generate a referral code via API\n- [ ] Code is 8-char alphanumeric by default, collision-checked with retry\n- [ ] Player can optionally set a custom code (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`, unique)\n- [ ] Each player has exactly one active code (generating a new one replaces the old one)\n- [ ] Code is persisted in `referral_codes` table\n\n### FR-2: Referral Linking\n\nWhen a player signs up or connects their wallet via a referral link (`taunt.bet/r/CODE`), they are permanently linked to the referrer. Alternatively, a player can manually enter a referral code in their settings.\n\n**Rules:**\n- One referrer per player, immutable once set\n- First code applied wins — cannot change referrer\n- Self-referral blocked (same wallet cannot be both referrer and referee)\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Visiting `taunt.bet/r/{CODE}` stores the code (localStorage) until the player authenticates\n- [ ] On authentication, if the player has no referrer and a stored/submitted code exists, the link is created\n- [ ] Player can manually enter a referral code via API (settings page)\n- [ ] Attempting to change an existing referrer returns an error\n- [ ] Self-referral (referrer wallet = referee wallet) is rejected\n- [ ] Referral link is stored in `referral_links` table with `created_at` timestamp\n\n### FR-3: Referee Fee Rebate\n","numLines":100,"startLine":1,"totalLines":717}}}
