{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01919Webyo2gNS3ez65657Dw","type":"tool_result","content":"   200→    activeCount: number,\n   201→    totalVolumeLamports: string,\n   202→    totalEarnedLamports: string,\n   203→    pendingLamports: string\n   204→  }\n   205→\n   206→GET  /referral/earnings            — Get detailed per-game earnings log\n   207→  Query: { page?: number, limit?: number }\n   208→  Response: {\n   209→    items: [{\n   210→      roundId: string,\n   211→      gameType: string,\n   212→      refereeWallet: string,\n   213→      wagerLamports: string,\n   214→      earnedLamports: string,\n   215→      createdAt: string\n   216→    }],\n   217→    pagination: { page: number, totalPages: number }\n   218→  }\n   219→\n   220→POST /referral/claim               — Request earnings claim (async via queue)\n   221→  Response: { claimId: string, amountLamports: string, status: \"pending\" }\n   222→\n   223→GET  /referral/claim/:claimId      — Poll claim status\n   224→  Response: { claimId: string, amountLamports: string, status: \"pending\" | \"completed\" | \"failed\", txSignature?: string }\n   225→```\n   226→\n   227→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   228→- [ ] All endpoints require JWT authentication\n   229→- [ ] All endpoints return appropriate error codes (400 for bad input, 404 for not found, 409 for conflict)\n   230→- [ ] Rate limiting is applied to code generation and claim endpoints\n   231→- [ ] Monetary values use lamport strings (not floating point)\n   232→\n   233→### FR-8: Database Schema\n   234→\n   235→New tables for the referral system. All off-chain, no program changes.\n   236→\n   237→```sql\n   238→referral_codes (\n   239→  id            SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n   240→  wallet        TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,\n   241→  code          TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,\n   242→  custom        BOOLEAN DEFAULT false,\n   243→  created_at    TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n   244→  updated_at    TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\n   245→)\n   246→\n   247→referral_links (\n   248→  id              SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n   249→  referrer_wallet TEXT NOT NULL,\n   250→  referee_wallet  TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,  -- one referrer per player\n   251→  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\n   252→)\n   253→\n   254→referral_earnings (\n   255→  id                        SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n   256→  referrer_wallet           TEXT NOT NULL,\n   257→  referee_wallet            TEXT NOT NULL,\n   258→  round_id                  TEXT NOT NULL,\n   259→  game_type                 TEXT NOT NULL,\n   260→  wager_lamports            BIGINT NOT NULL,\n   261→  fee_lamports              BIGINT NOT NULL,\n   262→  referrer_earned_lamports  BIGINT NOT NULL,\n   263→  referrer_rate_bps         INTEGER NOT NULL,\n   264→  referee_rebate_lamports   BIGINT NOT NULL,\n   265→  referee_rebate_rate_bps   INTEGER NOT NULL,  -- always 1000 for v1\n   266→  created_at                TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n   267→  UNIQUE (referee_wallet, round_id)  -- idempotency: one earning per player per round\n   268→)\n   269→\n   270→referral_claims (\n   271→  id                UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),\n   272→  wallet            TEXT NOT NULL,\n   273→  amount_lamports   BIGINT NOT NULL,\n   274→  status            TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (status IN ('pending','processing','completed','failed')),\n   275→  tx_signature      TEXT,\n   276→  error             TEXT,\n   277→  requested_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n   278→  processed_at      TIMESTAMPTZ\n   279→)\n   280→\n   281→-- KOL custom referrer rates (overrides default 1000 bps)\n   282→referral_kol_rates (\n   283→  wallet          TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n   284→  rate_bps        INTEGER NOT NULL,  -- e.g., 2000 = 20% of total fee (= 100 bps of wager)\n   285→  set_by          TEXT NOT NULL,     -- admin wallet\n   286→  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n   287→  updated_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\n   288→)\n   289→```\n   290→\n   291→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   292→- [ ] All tables created via migration (referral_codes, referral_links, referral_earnings, referral_claims, referral_kol_rates)\n   293→- [ ] `referral_links.referee_wallet` has UNIQUE constraint (one referrer per player)\n   294→- [ ] `referral_codes.code` has UNIQUE constraint\n   295→- [ ] Appropriate indexes on wallet columns and `referral_earnings.round_id`\n   296→- [ ] `referral_earnings` has unique idempotency guard (`UNIQUE (referee_wallet, round_id)`)\n   297→- [ ] `referral_claims.status` constrained to `pending|processing|completed|failed`\n   298→\n   299→### FR-9: Frontend — Routes, Pages, and Components\n   300→\n   301→All frontend changes live in `apps/platform/`. Follows existing patterns: React Router routes in `App.tsx`, NavLink in `Sidebar.tsx`, feature code in `features/referral/`, API wrappers in `lib/referral-api.ts`.\n   302→\n   303→#### 9a. New Route: `/r/:code` — Referral Link Handler\n   304→\n   305→A lightweight route that captures the referral code from the URL, persists it, and redirects to the home page (or wherever the player was headed).\n   306→\n   307→**Flow:**\n   308→1. Player visits `taunt.bet/r/ABCD1234`\n   309→2. Route component reads `:code` via `useParams()`\n   310→3. Stores `{ code, capturedAt }` in `localStorage` key `referral_code`\n   311→4. Redirects to `/` via `<Navigate to=\"/\" replace />`\n   312→5. On next authentication (in `SessionContext` or a dedicated `useReferralApply` hook), if `referral_code` exists in localStorage and user has no referrer → calls `POST /referral/apply` → clears localStorage on success\n   313→\n   314→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   315→- [ ] Route `/r/:code` registered in `App.tsx`\n   316→- [ ] Code stored in localStorage on visit (no auth required)\n   317→- [ ] Redirect to `/` happens immediately after capture\n   318→- [ ] On successful authentication, stored code is applied via API\n   319→- [ ] localStorage is cleared after successful apply (or if code is invalid/already linked)\n   320→- [ ] Invalid/expired codes show a toast notification, not a blocking error\n   321→\n   322→#### 9b. Sidebar Navigation — Referrals Link\n   323→\n   324→New nav item in the \"Player\" section of `Sidebar.tsx`, between \"Quests\" and the \"Platform\" section.\n   325→\n   326→```tsx\n   327→<NavLink to=\"/referrals\" className={({ isActive }) => `nv-item ${isActive ? \"active\" : \"\"}`}\n   328→  style={{ \"--nc\": \"var(--color-green)\" } as React.CSSProperties}>\n   329→  <div className=\"nv-ico\">\n   330→    {/* share/link icon */}\n   331→  </div>\n   332→  <span className=\"nv-lbl\">Referrals</span>\n   333→</NavLink>\n   334→```\n   335→\n   336→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   337→- [ ] \"Referrals\" nav item appears in sidebar under \"Player\" section\n   338→- [ ] Active state styling matches existing nav items\n   339→- [ ] Icon is a share/link-style SVG consistent with sidebar icon style\n   340→- [ ] Navigates to `/referrals`\n   341→\n   342→#### 9c. Referral Page (`/referrals`)\n   343→\n   344→Main referral hub page at route `/referrals`. Requires wallet connection + authentication. Shows different states based on whether the player has generated a code yet.\n   345→\n   346→**Layout — top to bottom:**\n   347→\n   348→1. **Your Referral Link** (card)\n   349→   - If no code yet: \"Generate your referral link\" button → calls `POST /referral/code` → shows code"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"22eabd0a-3a3b-489d-bc57-d8e8d222d116","uuid":"a8168d07-42c4-45b8-ba8e-2a2f2e13fcf8","timestamp":"2026-03-24T21:23:25.062Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/300-referral-system/spec.md","content":"    activeCount: number,\n    totalVolumeLamports: string,\n    totalEarnedLamports: string,\n    pendingLamports: string\n  }\n\nGET  /referral/earnings            — Get detailed per-game earnings log\n  Query: { page?: number, limit?: number }\n  Response: {\n    items: [{\n      roundId: string,\n      gameType: string,\n      refereeWallet: string,\n      wagerLamports: string,\n      earnedLamports: string,\n      createdAt: string\n    }],\n    pagination: { page: number, totalPages: number }\n  }\n\nPOST /referral/claim               — Request earnings claim (async via queue)\n  Response: { claimId: string, amountLamports: string, status: \"pending\" }\n\nGET  /referral/claim/:claimId      — Poll claim status\n  Response: { claimId: string, amountLamports: string, status: \"pending\" | \"completed\" | \"failed\", txSignature?: string }\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] All endpoints require JWT authentication\n- [ ] All endpoints return appropriate error codes (400 for bad input, 404 for not found, 409 for conflict)\n- [ ] Rate limiting is applied to code generation and claim endpoints\n- [ ] Monetary values use lamport strings (not floating point)\n\n### FR-8: Database Schema\n\nNew tables for the referral system. All off-chain, no program changes.\n\n```sql\nreferral_codes (\n  id            SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n  wallet        TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,\n  code          TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,\n  custom        BOOLEAN DEFAULT false,\n  created_at    TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n  updated_at    TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\n)\n\nreferral_links (\n  id              SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n  referrer_wallet TEXT NOT NULL,\n  referee_wallet  TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,  -- one referrer per player\n  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\n)\n\nreferral_earnings (\n  id                        SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n  referrer_wallet           TEXT NOT NULL,\n  referee_wallet            TEXT NOT NULL,\n  round_id                  TEXT NOT NULL,\n  game_type                 TEXT NOT NULL,\n  wager_lamports            BIGINT NOT NULL,\n  fee_lamports              BIGINT NOT NULL,\n  referrer_earned_lamports  BIGINT NOT NULL,\n  referrer_rate_bps         INTEGER NOT NULL,\n  referee_rebate_lamports   BIGINT NOT NULL,\n  referee_rebate_rate_bps   INTEGER NOT NULL,  -- always 1000 for v1\n  created_at                TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n  UNIQUE (referee_wallet, round_id)  -- idempotency: one earning per player per round\n)\n\nreferral_claims (\n  id                UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),\n  wallet            TEXT NOT NULL,\n  amount_lamports   BIGINT NOT NULL,\n  status            TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (status IN ('pending','processing','completed','failed')),\n  tx_signature      TEXT,\n  error             TEXT,\n  requested_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n  processed_at      TIMESTAMPTZ\n)\n\n-- KOL custom referrer rates (overrides default 1000 bps)\nreferral_kol_rates (\n  wallet          TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  rate_bps        INTEGER NOT NULL,  -- e.g., 2000 = 20% of total fee (= 100 bps of wager)\n  set_by          TEXT NOT NULL,     -- admin wallet\n  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n  updated_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\n)\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] All tables created via migration (referral_codes, referral_links, referral_earnings, referral_claims, referral_kol_rates)\n- [ ] `referral_links.referee_wallet` has UNIQUE constraint (one referrer per player)\n- [ ] `referral_codes.code` has UNIQUE constraint\n- [ ] Appropriate indexes on wallet columns and `referral_earnings.round_id`\n- [ ] `referral_earnings` has unique idempotency guard (`UNIQUE (referee_wallet, round_id)`)\n- [ ] `referral_claims.status` constrained to `pending|processing|completed|failed`\n\n### FR-9: Frontend — Routes, Pages, and Components\n\nAll frontend changes live in `apps/platform/`. Follows existing patterns: React Router routes in `App.tsx`, NavLink in `Sidebar.tsx`, feature code in `features/referral/`, API wrappers in `lib/referral-api.ts`.\n\n#### 9a. New Route: `/r/:code` — Referral Link Handler\n\nA lightweight route that captures the referral code from the URL, persists it, and redirects to the home page (or wherever the player was headed).\n\n**Flow:**\n1. Player visits `taunt.bet/r/ABCD1234`\n2. Route component reads `:code` via `useParams()`\n3. Stores `{ code, capturedAt }` in `localStorage` key `referral_code`\n4. Redirects to `/` via `<Navigate to=\"/\" replace />`\n5. On next authentication (in `SessionContext` or a dedicated `useReferralApply` hook), if `referral_code` exists in localStorage and user has no referrer → calls `POST /referral/apply` → clears localStorage on success\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Route `/r/:code` registered in `App.tsx`\n- [ ] Code stored in localStorage on visit (no auth required)\n- [ ] Redirect to `/` happens immediately after capture\n- [ ] On successful authentication, stored code is applied via API\n- [ ] localStorage is cleared after successful apply (or if code is invalid/already linked)\n- [ ] Invalid/expired codes show a toast notification, not a blocking error\n\n#### 9b. Sidebar Navigation — Referrals Link\n\nNew nav item in the \"Player\" section of `Sidebar.tsx`, between \"Quests\" and the \"Platform\" section.\n\n```tsx\n<NavLink to=\"/referrals\" className={({ isActive }) => `nv-item ${isActive ? \"active\" : \"\"}`}\n  style={{ \"--nc\": \"var(--color-green)\" } as React.CSSProperties}>\n  <div className=\"nv-ico\">\n    {/* share/link icon */}\n  </div>\n  <span className=\"nv-lbl\">Referrals</span>\n</NavLink>\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] \"Referrals\" nav item appears in sidebar under \"Player\" section\n- [ ] Active state styling matches existing nav items\n- [ ] Icon is a share/link-style SVG consistent with sidebar icon style\n- [ ] Navigates to `/referrals`\n\n#### 9c. Referral Page (`/referrals`)\n\nMain referral hub page at route `/referrals`. Requires wallet connection + authentication. Shows different states based on whether the player has generated a code yet.\n\n**Layout — top to bottom:**\n\n1. **Your Referral Link** (card)\n   - If no code yet: \"Generate your referral link\" button → calls `POST /referral/code` → shows code","numLines":150,"startLine":200,"totalLines":717}}}
