{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GrvFu7JSQVxBHvYhiYgnEt","type":"tool_result","content":"   348→1. **Your Referral Link** (card)\n   349→   - If no code yet: \"Generate your referral link\" button → calls `POST /referral/code` → shows code\n   350→   - If code exists: display code + full URL in a styled input/box with a **Copy Link** button\n   351→   - Copy uses `navigator.clipboard.writeText(url)` with a brief \"Copied!\" feedback (tooltip or button text swap)\n   352→   - Optional: \"Customize code\" link → inline edit field to set custom code → calls `POST /referral/code { custom: \"...\" }`\n   353→\n   354→2. **Stats Summary** (card or stat row)\n   355→   - Four stat boxes in a row: Referred Players | Active (7d) | Total Volume | Total Earned\n   356→   - Values from `GET /referral/stats`\n   357→   - SOL values formatted with `BalanceDisplay` or equivalent (lamports → SOL, 4 decimal places)\n   358→   - Skeleton/loading state while fetching\n   359→\n   360→3. **Pending Earnings + Claim** (card)\n   361→   - Shows pending (unclaimed) balance prominently\n   362→   - \"Claim\" button — enabled only when pending > minimum threshold (0.01 SOL)\n   363→   - Claim flow: button → loading state → calls `POST /referral/claim` → success toast with tx link → refresh stats\n   364→   - Error state: if claim fails, show error message + retry option\n   365→\n   366→4. **Earnings History** (table)\n   367→   - Paginated table from `GET /referral/earnings`\n   368→   - Columns: Date | Game | Referee (truncated wallet) | Wager | Your Earning\n   369→   - Empty state: \"No earnings yet. Share your link to start earning!\"\n   370→   - Pagination controls at bottom (page numbers or \"Load more\")\n   371→\n   372→**Not-connected state:** Show a prompt to connect wallet + brief explanation of the referral program.\n   373→\n   374→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   375→- [ ] Route `/referrals` registered in `App.tsx`, renders `ReferralPage`\n   376→- [ ] Unauthenticated users see a connect-wallet prompt with referral program description\n   377→- [ ] Code generation works and displays the referral URL\n   378→- [ ] Copy button copies full URL to clipboard with visual feedback\n   379→- [ ] Custom code input validates (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`) and shows errors inline\n   380→- [ ] Stats summary loads from API and displays correctly with loading skeleton\n   381→- [ ] Claim button is disabled when below threshold, shows loading during claim\n   382→- [ ] Successful claim shows toast with transaction link (Solana explorer)\n   383→- [ ] Earnings table loads paginated data with correct columns\n   384→- [ ] Empty states have meaningful messages for each section\n   385→\n   386→#### 9d. Profile Settings — Referral Code Input\n   387→\n   388→In the existing profile page (`/profile`, settings tab), add a \"Referral Code\" section where players can manually enter a referral code if they didn't arrive via a referral link.\n   389→\n   390→**Layout:**\n   391→- Section header: \"Referral Code\"\n   392→- If no referrer linked: text input + \"Apply\" button\n   393→- If referrer already linked: display \"Referred by: [truncated wallet]\" (read-only)\n   394→- Error states: \"Invalid code\", \"Already linked to a referrer\", \"Cannot refer yourself\"\n   395→\n   396→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   397→- [ ] Referral code input section added to profile settings tab\n   398→- [ ] Input calls `POST /referral/apply` on submit\n   399→- [ ] If already referred, shows referrer wallet (read-only, non-editable)\n   400→- [ ] Validation errors display inline (not just console)\n   401→- [ ] Self-referral attempt shows clear error message\n   402→\n   403→#### 9e. API Client — `lib/referral-api.ts`\n   404→\n   405→Thin fetch wrappers following the pattern in `lib/auth-api.ts`. All calls require JWT from `useSession().accessToken`.\n   406→\n   407→```typescript\n   408→const BASE = import.meta.env.VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL ?? \"http://127.0.0.1:3100\";\n   409→\n   410→export async function generateReferralCode(token: string, custom?: string);\n   411→export async function getReferralCode(token: string);\n   412→export async function applyReferralCode(token: string, code: string);\n   413→export async function getReferralStats(token: string);\n   414→export async function getReferralEarnings(token: string, page?: number, limit?: number);\n   415→export async function requestReferralClaim(token: string);\n   416→export async function pollClaimStatus(token: string, claimId: string);\n   417→```\n   418→\n   419→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   420→- [ ] All 7 API functions implemented with JWT Bearer auth header\n   421→- [ ] Response parsing follows `parseResponse<T>()` pattern from `auth-api.ts`\n   422→- [ ] Error responses surface user-friendly messages (not raw HTTP status)\n   423→- [ ] Functions are typed with request/response interfaces\n   424→\n   425→#### 9f. Referral Apply Hook — `useReferralApply`\n   426→\n   427→A hook that runs on authentication to auto-apply stored referral codes from localStorage.\n   428→\n   429→```typescript\n   430→// In features/referral/hooks/useReferralApply.ts\n   431→export function useReferralApply() {\n   432→  const { isAuthenticated, accessToken } = useSession();\n   433→  const { address } = useWallet();\n   434→\n   435→  useEffect(() => {\n   436→    if (!isAuthenticated || !accessToken || !address) return;\n   437→    const stored = localStorage.getItem(\"referral_code\");\n   438→    if (!stored) return;\n   439→    const { code } = JSON.parse(stored);\n   440→    applyReferralCode(accessToken, code)\n   441→      .then(() => { localStorage.removeItem(\"referral_code\"); /* toast: linked! */ })\n   442→      .catch(() => { localStorage.removeItem(\"referral_code\"); /* silent or toast */ });\n   443→  }, [isAuthenticated, accessToken, address]);\n   444→}\n   445→```\n   446→\n   447→Mount in `App.tsx` (inside auth provider tree) so it runs globally on every login.\n   448→\n   449→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   450→- [ ] Hook reads referral code from localStorage after successful authentication\n   451→- [ ] Calls `POST /referral/apply` automatically\n   452→- [ ] Clears localStorage on success or permanent failure (invalid code, already linked)\n   453→- [ ] Does not clear localStorage on transient failure (network error) — retries next auth\n   454→- [ ] Shows a subtle success toast when a referral link is auto-applied\n   455→- [ ] Mounted in `App.tsx` or `AppContent` so it activates on any page\n   456→\n   457→### FR-10: Backend Settlement Integration\n   458→\n   459→The referral earnings calculation hooks into the existing settlement worker. No new services or workers needed.\n   460→\n   461→**Hook point:** After a game round/match settles successfully (settlement writes the outcome to DB), the settlement logic:\n   462→1. Looks up the player's referrer in `referral_links`\n   463→2. If referrer exists → calculates `referrer_earned_lamports = fee_lamports × referrer_rate_bps / 10000` (where fee_lamports = wager_lamports × fee_bps / 10000)\n   464→3. Inserts row into `referral_earnings`\n   465→4. Inserts `referral.game_settled` event into `event_queue` (same DB transaction) for downstream reward processing\n   466→\n   467→**Referrer rate lookup:**\n   468→1. Check `referral_kol_rates` for the referrer's wallet\n   469→2. If found → use KOL rate\n   470→3. If not → use default rate from config/env (default: 1000 bps = 10% of total fee = 50 bps of wager)\n   471→\n   472→**Performance:** Single DB query (join `referral_links` + optional `referral_kol_rates`) per settled game. Cached in-memory for hot wallets if needed later.\n   473→\n   474→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   475→- [ ] Settlement worker checks for referrer after each game settlement\n   476→- [ ] Referrer earnings are calculated using correct formula (bps of total fee, not total wager)\n   477→- [ ] KOL custom rate is used when present, default rate otherwise\n   478→- [ ] Earnings row is inserted in the same DB transaction as settlement (atomicity)\n   479→- [ ] Referral event emitted to async queue for downstream processing (referee rewards, notifications)\n   480→- [ ] No additional RPC calls — purely DB-level\n   481→- [ ] Settlement latency increase is negligible (< 5ms additional)\n   482→\n   483→---\n   484→\n   485→### FR-11: Referral Event Contracts + Handler Idempotency\n   486→\n   487→Referral feature handlers are queue consumers built on spec 301 infrastructure.\n   488→\n   489→**Event types (v1):**\n   490→- `referral.claim_requested` — emitted after claim request row is created. Handler sends SOL from treasury.\n   491→\n   492→Note: `referral.game_settled` earnings are written synchronously in the settlement transaction (same DB tx). No async handler needed for earnings — only for claims, where the SOL transfer is the slow/unreliable part.\n   493→\n   494→**Payload contract:**\n   495→\n   496→`referral.claim_requested`\n   497→```json\n   498→{\n   499→  \"claimId\": \"uuid\",\n   500→  \"wallet\": \"string\",\n   501→  \"amountLamports\": \"string\",\n   502→  \"requestedAt\": \"ISO-8601 timestamp\"\n   503→}\n   504→```\n   505→\n   506→**Idempotency key:** `referral:claim:{claimId}`\n   507→\n   508→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   509→- [ ] `referral.claim_requested` event emitted with the payload above when a claim is created\n   510→- [ ] Handler validates payload shape; malformed payloads are dead-lettered\n   511→- [ ] Handler performs idempotency check: if claim already completed/failed, no-op\n   512→- [ ] Handler re-verifies available balance before transfer (prevents overpay on concurrent claims)\n   513→- [ ] Handler sends SOL from treasury to wallet, records tx_signature in `referral_claims`\n   514→- [ ] Re-processing the same event is a safe no-op (no duplicate SOL transfers)\n   515→\n   516→---\n   517→\n   518→## Design Decisions (v1)\n   519→\n   520→### Why immutable referrer linkage\n   521→\n   522→- Prevents referral hijacking and user confusion.\n   523→- Simplifies all downstream aggregation and payout logic.\n   524→- Keeps fraud analysis tractable (single parent per user graph).\n   525→\n   526→### Why async claims (not synchronous transfer API)\n   527→\n   528→- Wallet RPC operations are the slowest and least reliable part of the flow.\n   529→- Async queue gives retries/backoff and keeps user request latency low.\n   530→- Prevents backend API threads from being tied up by treasury transfer delays.\n   531→\n   532→### Why persist economic inputs in `referral_earnings`\n   533→\n   534→- Store `fee_lamports` + `referrer_rate_bps` with each earning row to preserve historical correctness.\n   535→- Future rate changes do not retroactively affect past earnings or audits.\n   536→- Makes dispute/debug workflows deterministic from DB data alone.\n   537→\n   538→---\n   539→\n   540→## Success Criteria\n   541→\n   542→- Players can generate, share, and apply referral codes without friction\n   543→- Referral earnings are calculated correctly and match expected economics (1000 bps of total fee = 50 bps of wager)\n   544→- Claim flow delivers SOL to the player's wallet reliably\n   545→- System handles concurrent operations without double-crediting or double-claiming\n   546→- No on-chain program changes required — entirely off-chain for v1\n   547→- Settlement path latency is not measurably affected by referral logic\n   548→- Rewards and claims are processed async via event queue (spec 301) without blocking game loops\n   549→\n   550→---\n   551→\n   552→## Dependencies\n   553→\n   554→- Existing JWT authentication system (spec 007)\n   555→- **Async event queue (spec 301)** — referee rewards and claim payouts are processed via the queue\n   556→- Backend settlement worker (must be extended with referral earnings hook + event emission)\n   557→- Treasury wallet with sufficient SOL for claim payouts\n   558→- Frontend routing for `/r/{CODE}` deep links\n   559→- Environment variables for default referral rate (`REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS=1000`) and claim threshold (`REFERRAL_MIN_CLAIM_LAMPORTS=10000000`)\n   560→\n   561→## Assumptions\n   562→\n   563→- Fee structure is 500 bps (5%) flat fee to single treasury (PlatformConfig on-chain)\n   564→- Treasury wallet is funded and managed outside this spec\n   565→- Referral system launches alongside or after existing games (coinflip, lord-of-rngs)\n   566→- No on-chain enforcement of referral economics needed for v1\n   567→- Postgres `SKIP LOCKED` is available (Postgres 9.5+ — already met)\n   568→\n   569→---\n   570→\n   571→## Validation Plan\n   572→\n   573→| # | Acceptance Criterion | Validation Method | Evidence Required |\n   574→|---|---------------------|-------------------|-------------------|\n   575→| 1 | Code generation works | API test: generate code, verify format and DB entry | Test output |\n   576→| 2 | Custom codes validated | API test: valid/invalid custom codes | Test output |\n   577→| 3 | Referral linking via URL | E2E: visit /r/CODE, authenticate, verify link created | Test output + DB check |\n   578→| 4 | Manual code entry works | API test: apply code via endpoint | Test output |\n   579→| 5 | Self-referral blocked | API test: apply own code, expect 400 | Test output |\n   580→| 6 | Immutable referrer | API test: apply second code after first, expect 409 | Test output |\n   581→| 7 | Earnings calculated at settlement | Integration test: settle game for referred player, check referral_earnings | Test output + DB check |\n   582→| 8 | KOL custom rate applied | Integration test: set KOL rate, settle game, verify different earning | Test output |\n   583→| 9 | Stats endpoint accurate | API test: create referrals + earnings, verify stats math | Test output |\n   584→| 10 | Claim delivers SOL | Integration test: claim flow, verify tx on-chain | Tx signature |\n   585→| 11 | Concurrent claim prevention | Load test: parallel claims, verify only one succeeds | Test output |\n   586→| 12 | Referee bonus reward granted | Integration test: apply code + complete game, verify reward trigger fired via queue | Test output + DB check |\n   587→| 21 | Async claim completes via queue | Integration test: POST claim → poll status → verify completed with tx sig | Test output + Tx sig |\n   588→| 22 | Welcome reward fires on code apply | Integration test: apply code → verify `referral.code_applied` event processed | Test output + DB check |\n   589→| 23 | Queue infrastructure works (spec 301) | See spec 301 validation plan | Per spec 301 |\n   590→| 13 | `/r/:code` captures + redirects | E2E: visit referral URL, check localStorage, verify redirect to `/` | Browser test |\n   591→| 14 | Auto-apply on auth | E2E: store code in localStorage, connect wallet, verify referral link created + localStorage cleared | Browser test |\n   592→| 15 | Referral page renders all sections | Visual test: code card, stats, claim, earnings table in correct layout | Screenshot |\n   593→| 16 | Copy link works | E2E: click copy button, verify clipboard content matches referral URL | Browser test |\n   594→| 17 | Sidebar nav item present | Visual test: \"Referrals\" link visible in Player section, active state works | Screenshot |\n   595→| 18 | Profile settings code input | E2E: enter code in profile settings, verify referral linked | Browser test |\n   596→| 19 | Unauthenticated state | Visual test: `/referrals` without wallet shows connect prompt | Screenshot |\n   597→| 20 | Claim button states | E2E: disabled when below threshold, loading during claim, success toast with tx link | Browser test |\n   598→\n   599→---\n   600→\n   601→## Completion Signal\n   602→\n   603→### Implementation Checklist\n   604→\n   605→#### Prerequisite\n   606→- [x] [backend] Event queue infrastructure implemented per spec 301 (completed in spec 301)\n   607→\n   608→#### Backend — Database & Core\n   609→- [ ] [backend] Database migration `011_referral.sql`: create `referral_codes`, `referral_links`, `referral_earnings`, `referral_claims`, `referral_kol_rates` tables with all constraints and indexes per FR-8\n   610→- [ ] [backend] DB client methods in `db.ts`: `insertReferralCode`, `getReferralCodeByWallet`, `getReferralCodeByCode`, `upsertReferralCode` for code CRUD\n   611→- [ ] [backend] DB client methods: `insertReferralLink`, `getReferralLinkByReferee`, referral link queries\n   612→- [ ] [backend] DB client methods: `insertReferralEarning`, `getPendingBalance(wallet)` (sum referrer_earned where wallet=referrer + sum referee_rebate where wallet=referee, minus completed claims), `getReferralEarnings(wallet, page, limit)`, `getReferralStats(wallet)`\n   613→- [ ] [backend] DB client methods: `insertReferralClaim`, `getReferralClaim`, `updateClaimStatus`, `getReferrerRate(wallet)` (check kol_rates, fallback to env default)\n   614→\n   615→#### Backend — API Endpoints\n   616→- [ ] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `POST /referral/code` — generate 8-char code (collision-retry) or set custom code (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`). Requires JWT auth. Returns `{ code, url }` (FR-1, FR-7)\n   617→- [ ] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/code` — return current code for authenticated wallet, or 404 (FR-7)\n   618→- [ ] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `POST /referral/apply` — link referee to referrer. Validate: code exists, no self-referral, no existing referrer. Returns `{ referrer, benefit: \"10% fee rebate on all games\" }` (FR-2, FR-7)\n   619→- [ ] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/stats` — return referredCount, activeCount (7d), totalVolumeLamports, totalEarnedLamports, pendingLamports for authenticated wallet. All values as lamport strings (FR-5, FR-7)\n   620→- [ ] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/earnings` — paginated per-game earnings log with roundId, gameType, refereeWallet, wagerLamports, earnedLamports, createdAt. Query params: page, limit (FR-5, FR-7)\n   621→- [ ] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `POST /referral/claim` — validate pending balance > min threshold (env `REFERRAL_MIN_CLAIM_LAMPORTS`, default 10M = 0.01 SOL), snapshot amount, insert claim row + emit `referral.claim_requested` event in same DB tx. Return 202 `{ claimId, amountLamports, status: \"pending\" }` (FR-6, FR-7)\n   622→- [ ] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/claim/:claimId` — return claim status + txSignature if completed (FR-7)\n   623→- [ ] [backend] Register referral routes in `index.ts`, mount at `/referral` prefix with JWT auth middleware\n   624→\n   625→#### Backend — Settlement Integration\n   626→- [ ] [backend] Settlement hook in `settle-tx.ts`: after each game settlement DB write, check `referral_links` for the settled player(s). If referrer exists, calculate `referrer_earned = fee_lamports * referrer_rate_bps / 10000` and `referee_rebate = fee_lamports * 1000 / 10000` (fixed 10%). Insert into `referral_earnings` in the same DB transaction. Use `getReferrerRate(wallet)` for KOL override (FR-4, FR-10)\n   627→- [ ] [backend] Wrap settlement DB writes in `sql.transaction()` for atomicity — referral earning insert MUST be in the same transaction as the game settlement update (FR-10 + System Invariant 4)\n   628→\n   629→#### Backend — Claim Queue Handler\n   630→- [ ] [backend] Register `referral.claim_requested` handler in queue registry: load claim by ID, verify status is `pending`, update to `processing`, re-verify available balance >= claim amount, execute SOL transfer from server keypair (treasury) to wallet, record tx_signature, update status to `completed`. On failure: record error, update status to `failed`. Idempotent: skip if status is already `completed` (FR-6, FR-11)\n   631→\n   632→#### Frontend — API Client & Plumbing\n   633→- [ ] [frontend] `lib/referral-api.ts` — 7 typed fetch wrappers with JWT Bearer auth following `auth-api.ts` pattern: `generateReferralCode`, `getReferralCode`, `applyReferralCode`, `getReferralStats`, `getReferralEarnings`, `requestReferralClaim`, `pollClaimStatus` (FR-9e)\n   634→- [ ] [frontend] `/r/:code` route in `App.tsx` — capture code to `localStorage` key `referral_code` as `{ code, capturedAt }`, redirect to `/` via `<Navigate replace />` (FR-9a)\n   635→- [ ] [frontend] `useReferralApply` hook — on authentication, if `referral_code` in localStorage and user has no referrer, call `POST /referral/apply`. Clear localStorage on success or permanent failure (invalid/already linked). Keep on transient failure. Show success toast. Mount in `App.tsx` inside auth provider tree (FR-9f)\n   636→\n   637→#### Frontend — Referral Page\n   638→- [ ] [frontend] Sidebar nav item \"Referrals\" in Player section of `Sidebar.tsx` with share/link icon, `--nc: var(--color-green)`, navigates to `/referrals` (FR-9b)\n   639→- [ ] [frontend] `/referrals` route + `ReferralPage` shell: unauthenticated state shows connect-wallet prompt with referral program description. Authenticated state renders feature sections. Wrap in `RouteErrorBoundary` (FR-9c)\n   640→- [ ] [frontend] Referral page §1: \"Your Referral Link\" card — generate code button (if none), display code + full URL + Copy Link button with clipboard feedback. Custom code edit with inline validation (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`) (FR-9c §1)\n   641→- [ ] [frontend] Referral page §2: Stats summary card — four stat boxes (Referred Players, Active 7d, Total Volume, Total Earned) from `GET /referral/stats`. SOL values via lamports→SOL formatting. Loading skeleton (FR-9c §2)\n   642→- [ ] [frontend] Referral page §3: Pending balance card — show unified pending balance prominently. Breakdown: \"From referrals: X SOL\" + \"From fee rebates: Y SOL\". Claim button disabled below threshold, loading during claim, success toast with Solana explorer tx link (FR-9c §3, FR-6)\n   643→- [ ] [frontend] Referral page §4: Earnings history table — paginated from `GET /referral/earnings`. Columns: Date, Game, Referee (truncated wallet), Wager, Your Earning. Empty state message. Pagination controls (FR-9c §4)\n   644→- [ ] [frontend] Profile settings: \"Referral Code\" section in profile settings tab. If no referrer: input + Apply button. If already referred: read-only \"Referred by: [wallet]\". Error states inline (FR-9d)\n   645→\n   646→#### Testing\n   647→- [ ] [test] Backend unit tests for referral routes: code generation, apply (happy path + self-referral + duplicate), stats, earnings pagination, claim flow (happy + zero balance + below threshold + concurrent)\n   648→- [ ] [test] Backend integration test: settle a game for a referred player → verify `referral_earnings` row with correct referrer_earned + referee_rebate amounts\n   649→- [ ] [test] Add local deterministic E2E coverage for primary user flow(s) in `e2e/local/**` (or mark N/A with reason for non-web/non-interactive specs)\n   650→- [ ] [test] Add visual route/state coverage in `e2e/visual/**`; run `pnpm test:visual` and update baselines only for intentional UI changes\n   651→- [ ] [test] Update visual baselines for `/referrals` page (new page) and sidebar (new nav item). Run `pnpm test:visual` to identify failures, then `pnpm test:visual:update` to regenerate. **Before committing**: read old baseline and new screenshot for each changed page (use Read tool on PNG files). Evaluate: **PASS** (changes clearly match spec intent) → commit; **REVIEW** (unexpected areas changed) → save diff images to `docs/specs/300-referral-system/visual-review/`, describe concerns; **FAIL** → fix code\n   652→- [ ] [test] If external provider/oracle/VRF integration is included, add devnet real-provider E2E coverage in `e2e/devnet/**` with env validation + retry/backoff (or mark N/A with reason)\n   653→\n   654→### Testing Requirements\n   655→\n   656→The agent MUST complete ALL before outputting the completion signal:\n   657→\n   658→#### Code Quality\n   659→- [ ] All existing tests pass\n   660→- [ ] New tests added for new functionality\n   661→- [ ] No lint errors\n   662→\n   663→#### Functional Verification\n   664→- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified\n   665→- [ ] Edge cases handled\n   666→- [ ] Error states handled\n   667→\n   668→#### Visual Regression\n   669→- [ ] `pnpm test:visual` passes (all baselines match)\n   670→- [ ] If this spec changes UI: affected baselines regenerated and committed\n   671→- [ ] Local deterministic E2E passes (`pnpm test:e2e`) for user-facing flows, or N/A documented\n   672→- [ ] Devnet real-provider E2E passes (`pnpm test:e2e:devnet`) when provider-backed flows are included\n   673→\n   674→#### Visual Verification (if UI)\n   675→- [ ] Desktop view correct\n   676→- [ ] Mobile view correct\n   677→\n   678→#### Console/Network Check (if web)\n   679→- [ ] No JS console errors\n   680→- [ ] No failed network requests\n   681→\n   682→#### Smoke Test (Human-in-the-Loop)\n   683→\n   684→Before declaring done, trace every user-facing flow and verify the experience\n   685→makes sense from a player's perspective.\n   686→\n   687→- [ ] Generate referral code → copy link → verify URL format\n   688→- [ ] Visit referral link in incognito → authenticate → verify referrer linked\n   689→- [ ] Manually enter code in settings → verify referrer linked\n   690→- [ ] Play a game as referred player → verify referrer earnings appear\n   691→- [ ] Referrer dashboard shows correct stats\n   692→- [ ] Claim earnings → verify SOL arrives in wallet\n   693→- [ ] Attempt self-referral → verify blocked\n   694→- [ ] Attempt to change referrer → verify blocked\n   695→- [ ] Referee fee rebate accrues after playing a game (visible in pending balance)\n   696→- [ ] Referral page shows breakdown: \"From referrals: X\" + \"From fee rebates: Y\"\n   697→\n   698→### Iteration Instructions\n   699→\n   700→If ANY check fails:\n   701→1. Identify the specific issue\n   702→2. Fix the code\n   703→3. Re-run tests\n   704→4. Re-verify all criteria\n   705→5. Check again\n   706→\n   707→**Only when ALL checks pass, output:** `<promise>DONE</promise>`\n   708→\n   709→### Post-Completion: Gap Analysis\n   710→\n   711→After the spec loop outputs `<promise>DONE</promise>`, `spec-loop.sh` automatically runs\n   712→`/gap-analysis {id} --non-interactive` which:\n   713→1. Audits every FR acceptance criterion against the codebase\n   714→2. Writes `docs/specs/{id}/gap-analysis.md` with inventory + audit + recommendations\n   715→3. Annotates FR checkboxes with HTML comment evidence (`<!-- satisfied: ... -->`)\n   716→4. Commits everything together with the completion commit\n   717→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"22eabd0a-3a3b-489d-bc57-d8e8d222d116","uuid":"16b3bc36-2177-4505-9f02-c70918d5d457","timestamp":"2026-03-24T21:23:28.971Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/300-referral-system/spec.md","content":"1. **Your Referral Link** (card)\n   - If no code yet: \"Generate your referral link\" button → calls `POST /referral/code` → shows code\n   - If code exists: display code + full URL in a styled input/box with a **Copy Link** button\n   - Copy uses `navigator.clipboard.writeText(url)` with a brief \"Copied!\" feedback (tooltip or button text swap)\n   - Optional: \"Customize code\" link → inline edit field to set custom code → calls `POST /referral/code { custom: \"...\" }`\n\n2. **Stats Summary** (card or stat row)\n   - Four stat boxes in a row: Referred Players | Active (7d) | Total Volume | Total Earned\n   - Values from `GET /referral/stats`\n   - SOL values formatted with `BalanceDisplay` or equivalent (lamports → SOL, 4 decimal places)\n   - Skeleton/loading state while fetching\n\n3. **Pending Earnings + Claim** (card)\n   - Shows pending (unclaimed) balance prominently\n   - \"Claim\" button — enabled only when pending > minimum threshold (0.01 SOL)\n   - Claim flow: button → loading state → calls `POST /referral/claim` → success toast with tx link → refresh stats\n   - Error state: if claim fails, show error message + retry option\n\n4. **Earnings History** (table)\n   - Paginated table from `GET /referral/earnings`\n   - Columns: Date | Game | Referee (truncated wallet) | Wager | Your Earning\n   - Empty state: \"No earnings yet. Share your link to start earning!\"\n   - Pagination controls at bottom (page numbers or \"Load more\")\n\n**Not-connected state:** Show a prompt to connect wallet + brief explanation of the referral program.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Route `/referrals` registered in `App.tsx`, renders `ReferralPage`\n- [ ] Unauthenticated users see a connect-wallet prompt with referral program description\n- [ ] Code generation works and displays the referral URL\n- [ ] Copy button copies full URL to clipboard with visual feedback\n- [ ] Custom code input validates (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`) and shows errors inline\n- [ ] Stats summary loads from API and displays correctly with loading skeleton\n- [ ] Claim button is disabled when below threshold, shows loading during claim\n- [ ] Successful claim shows toast with transaction link (Solana explorer)\n- [ ] Earnings table loads paginated data with correct columns\n- [ ] Empty states have meaningful messages for each section\n\n#### 9d. Profile Settings — Referral Code Input\n\nIn the existing profile page (`/profile`, settings tab), add a \"Referral Code\" section where players can manually enter a referral code if they didn't arrive via a referral link.\n\n**Layout:**\n- Section header: \"Referral Code\"\n- If no referrer linked: text input + \"Apply\" button\n- If referrer already linked: display \"Referred by: [truncated wallet]\" (read-only)\n- Error states: \"Invalid code\", \"Already linked to a referrer\", \"Cannot refer yourself\"\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Referral code input section added to profile settings tab\n- [ ] Input calls `POST /referral/apply` on submit\n- [ ] If already referred, shows referrer wallet (read-only, non-editable)\n- [ ] Validation errors display inline (not just console)\n- [ ] Self-referral attempt shows clear error message\n\n#### 9e. API Client — `lib/referral-api.ts`\n\nThin fetch wrappers following the pattern in `lib/auth-api.ts`. All calls require JWT from `useSession().accessToken`.\n\n```typescript\nconst BASE = import.meta.env.VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL ?? \"http://127.0.0.1:3100\";\n\nexport async function generateReferralCode(token: string, custom?: string);\nexport async function getReferralCode(token: string);\nexport async function applyReferralCode(token: string, code: string);\nexport async function getReferralStats(token: string);\nexport async function getReferralEarnings(token: string, page?: number, limit?: number);\nexport async function requestReferralClaim(token: string);\nexport async function pollClaimStatus(token: string, claimId: string);\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] All 7 API functions implemented with JWT Bearer auth header\n- [ ] Response parsing follows `parseResponse<T>()` pattern from `auth-api.ts`\n- [ ] Error responses surface user-friendly messages (not raw HTTP status)\n- [ ] Functions are typed with request/response interfaces\n\n#### 9f. Referral Apply Hook — `useReferralApply`\n\nA hook that runs on authentication to auto-apply stored referral codes from localStorage.\n\n```typescript\n// In features/referral/hooks/useReferralApply.ts\nexport function useReferralApply() {\n  const { isAuthenticated, accessToken } = useSession();\n  const { address } = useWallet();\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (!isAuthenticated || !accessToken || !address) return;\n    const stored = localStorage.getItem(\"referral_code\");\n    if (!stored) return;\n    const { code } = JSON.parse(stored);\n    applyReferralCode(accessToken, code)\n      .then(() => { localStorage.removeItem(\"referral_code\"); /* toast: linked! */ })\n      .catch(() => { localStorage.removeItem(\"referral_code\"); /* silent or toast */ });\n  }, [isAuthenticated, accessToken, address]);\n}\n```\n\nMount in `App.tsx` (inside auth provider tree) so it runs globally on every login.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Hook reads referral code from localStorage after successful authentication\n- [ ] Calls `POST /referral/apply` automatically\n- [ ] Clears localStorage on success or permanent failure (invalid code, already linked)\n- [ ] Does not clear localStorage on transient failure (network error) — retries next auth\n- [ ] Shows a subtle success toast when a referral link is auto-applied\n- [ ] Mounted in `App.tsx` or `AppContent` so it activates on any page\n\n### FR-10: Backend Settlement Integration\n\nThe referral earnings calculation hooks into the existing settlement worker. No new services or workers needed.\n\n**Hook point:** After a game round/match settles successfully (settlement writes the outcome to DB), the settlement logic:\n1. Looks up the player's referrer in `referral_links`\n2. If referrer exists → calculates `referrer_earned_lamports = fee_lamports × referrer_rate_bps / 10000` (where fee_lamports = wager_lamports × fee_bps / 10000)\n3. Inserts row into `referral_earnings`\n4. Inserts `referral.game_settled` event into `event_queue` (same DB transaction) for downstream reward processing\n\n**Referrer rate lookup:**\n1. Check `referral_kol_rates` for the referrer's wallet\n2. If found → use KOL rate\n3. If not → use default rate from config/env (default: 1000 bps = 10% of total fee = 50 bps of wager)\n\n**Performance:** Single DB query (join `referral_links` + optional `referral_kol_rates`) per settled game. Cached in-memory for hot wallets if needed later.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Settlement worker checks for referrer after each game settlement\n- [ ] Referrer earnings are calculated using correct formula (bps of total fee, not total wager)\n- [ ] KOL custom rate is used when present, default rate otherwise\n- [ ] Earnings row is inserted in the same DB transaction as settlement (atomicity)\n- [ ] Referral event emitted to async queue for downstream processing (referee rewards, notifications)\n- [ ] No additional RPC calls — purely DB-level\n- [ ] Settlement latency increase is negligible (< 5ms additional)\n\n---\n\n### FR-11: Referral Event Contracts + Handler Idempotency\n\nReferral feature handlers are queue consumers built on spec 301 infrastructure.\n\n**Event types (v1):**\n- `referral.claim_requested` — emitted after claim request row is created. Handler sends SOL from treasury.\n\nNote: `referral.game_settled` earnings are written synchronously in the settlement transaction (same DB tx). No async handler needed for earnings — only for claims, where the SOL transfer is the slow/unreliable part.\n\n**Payload contract:**\n\n`referral.claim_requested`\n```json\n{\n  \"claimId\": \"uuid\",\n  \"wallet\": \"string\",\n  \"amountLamports\": \"string\",\n  \"requestedAt\": \"ISO-8601 timestamp\"\n}\n```\n\n**Idempotency key:** `referral:claim:{claimId}`\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] `referral.claim_requested` event emitted with the payload above when a claim is created\n- [ ] Handler validates payload shape; malformed payloads are dead-lettered\n- [ ] Handler performs idempotency check: if claim already completed/failed, no-op\n- [ ] Handler re-verifies available balance before transfer (prevents overpay on concurrent claims)\n- [ ] Handler sends SOL from treasury to wallet, records tx_signature in `referral_claims`\n- [ ] Re-processing the same event is a safe no-op (no duplicate SOL transfers)\n\n---\n\n## Design Decisions (v1)\n\n### Why immutable referrer linkage\n\n- Prevents referral hijacking and user confusion.\n- Simplifies all downstream aggregation and payout logic.\n- Keeps fraud analysis tractable (single parent per user graph).\n\n### Why async claims (not synchronous transfer API)\n\n- Wallet RPC operations are the slowest and least reliable part of the flow.\n- Async queue gives retries/backoff and keeps user request latency low.\n- Prevents backend API threads from being tied up by treasury transfer delays.\n\n### Why persist economic inputs in `referral_earnings`\n\n- Store `fee_lamports` + `referrer_rate_bps` with each earning row to preserve historical correctness.\n- Future rate changes do not retroactively affect past earnings or audits.\n- Makes dispute/debug workflows deterministic from DB data alone.\n\n---\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- Players can generate, share, and apply referral codes without friction\n- Referral earnings are calculated correctly and match expected economics (1000 bps of total fee = 50 bps of wager)\n- Claim flow delivers SOL to the player's wallet reliably\n- System handles concurrent operations without double-crediting or double-claiming\n- No on-chain program changes required — entirely off-chain for v1\n- Settlement path latency is not measurably affected by referral logic\n- Rewards and claims are processed async via event queue (spec 301) without blocking game loops\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Existing JWT authentication system (spec 007)\n- **Async event queue (spec 301)** — referee rewards and claim payouts are processed via the queue\n- Backend settlement worker (must be extended with referral earnings hook + event emission)\n- Treasury wallet with sufficient SOL for claim payouts\n- Frontend routing for `/r/{CODE}` deep links\n- Environment variables for default referral rate (`REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS=1000`) and claim threshold (`REFERRAL_MIN_CLAIM_LAMPORTS=10000000`)\n\n## Assumptions\n\n- Fee structure is 500 bps (5%) flat fee to single treasury (PlatformConfig on-chain)\n- Treasury wallet is funded and managed outside this spec\n- Referral system launches alongside or after existing games (coinflip, lord-of-rngs)\n- No on-chain enforcement of referral economics needed for v1\n- Postgres `SKIP LOCKED` is available (Postgres 9.5+ — already met)\n\n---\n\n## Validation Plan\n\n| # | Acceptance Criterion | Validation Method | Evidence Required |\n|---|---------------------|-------------------|-------------------|\n| 1 | Code generation works | API test: generate code, verify format and DB entry | Test output |\n| 2 | Custom codes validated | API test: valid/invalid custom codes | Test output |\n| 3 | Referral linking via URL | E2E: visit /r/CODE, authenticate, verify link created | Test output + DB check |\n| 4 | Manual code entry works | API test: apply code via endpoint | Test output |\n| 5 | Self-referral blocked | API test: apply own code, expect 400 | Test output |\n| 6 | Immutable referrer | API test: apply second code after first, expect 409 | Test output |\n| 7 | Earnings calculated at settlement | Integration test: settle game for referred player, check referral_earnings | Test output + DB check |\n| 8 | KOL custom rate applied | Integration test: set KOL rate, settle game, verify different earning | Test output |\n| 9 | Stats endpoint accurate | API test: create referrals + earnings, verify stats math | Test output |\n| 10 | Claim delivers SOL | Integration test: claim flow, verify tx on-chain | Tx signature |\n| 11 | Concurrent claim prevention | Load test: parallel claims, verify only one succeeds | Test output |\n| 12 | Referee bonus reward granted | Integration test: apply code + complete game, verify reward trigger fired via queue | Test output + DB check |\n| 21 | Async claim completes via queue | Integration test: POST claim → poll status → verify completed with tx sig | Test output + Tx sig |\n| 22 | Welcome reward fires on code apply | Integration test: apply code → verify `referral.code_applied` event processed | Test output + DB check |\n| 23 | Queue infrastructure works (spec 301) | See spec 301 validation plan | Per spec 301 |\n| 13 | `/r/:code` captures + redirects | E2E: visit referral URL, check localStorage, verify redirect to `/` | Browser test |\n| 14 | Auto-apply on auth | E2E: store code in localStorage, connect wallet, verify referral link created + localStorage cleared | Browser test |\n| 15 | Referral page renders all sections | Visual test: code card, stats, claim, earnings table in correct layout | Screenshot |\n| 16 | Copy link works | E2E: click copy button, verify clipboard content matches referral URL | Browser test |\n| 17 | Sidebar nav item present | Visual test: \"Referrals\" link visible in Player section, active state works | Screenshot |\n| 18 | Profile settings code input | E2E: enter code in profile settings, verify referral linked | Browser test |\n| 19 | Unauthenticated state | Visual test: `/referrals` without wallet shows connect prompt | Screenshot |\n| 20 | Claim button states | E2E: disabled when below threshold, loading during claim, success toast with tx link | Browser test |\n\n---\n\n## Completion Signal\n\n### Implementation Checklist\n\n#### Prerequisite\n- [x] [backend] Event queue infrastructure implemented per spec 301 (completed in spec 301)\n\n#### Backend — Database & Core\n- [ ] [backend] Database migration `011_referral.sql`: create `referral_codes`, `referral_links`, `referral_earnings`, `referral_claims`, `referral_kol_rates` tables with all constraints and indexes per FR-8\n- [ ] [backend] DB client methods in `db.ts`: `insertReferralCode`, `getReferralCodeByWallet`, `getReferralCodeByCode`, `upsertReferralCode` for code CRUD\n- [ ] [backend] DB client methods: `insertReferralLink`, `getReferralLinkByReferee`, referral link queries\n- [ ] [backend] DB client methods: `insertReferralEarning`, `getPendingBalance(wallet)` (sum referrer_earned where wallet=referrer + sum referee_rebate where wallet=referee, minus completed claims), `getReferralEarnings(wallet, page, limit)`, `getReferralStats(wallet)`\n- [ ] [backend] DB client methods: `insertReferralClaim`, `getReferralClaim`, `updateClaimStatus`, `getReferrerRate(wallet)` (check kol_rates, fallback to env default)\n\n#### Backend — API Endpoints\n- [ ] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `POST /referral/code` — generate 8-char code (collision-retry) or set custom code (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`). Requires JWT auth. Returns `{ code, url }` (FR-1, FR-7)\n- [ ] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/code` — return current code for authenticated wallet, or 404 (FR-7)\n- [ ] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `POST /referral/apply` — link referee to referrer. Validate: code exists, no self-referral, no existing referrer. Returns `{ referrer, benefit: \"10% fee rebate on all games\" }` (FR-2, FR-7)\n- [ ] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/stats` — return referredCount, activeCount (7d), totalVolumeLamports, totalEarnedLamports, pendingLamports for authenticated wallet. All values as lamport strings (FR-5, FR-7)\n- [ ] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/earnings` — paginated per-game earnings log with roundId, gameType, refereeWallet, wagerLamports, earnedLamports, createdAt. Query params: page, limit (FR-5, FR-7)\n- [ ] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `POST /referral/claim` — validate pending balance > min threshold (env `REFERRAL_MIN_CLAIM_LAMPORTS`, default 10M = 0.01 SOL), snapshot amount, insert claim row + emit `referral.claim_requested` event in same DB tx. Return 202 `{ claimId, amountLamports, status: \"pending\" }` (FR-6, FR-7)\n- [ ] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/claim/:claimId` — return claim status + txSignature if completed (FR-7)\n- [ ] [backend] Register referral routes in `index.ts`, mount at `/referral` prefix with JWT auth middleware\n\n#### Backend — Settlement Integration\n- [ ] [backend] Settlement hook in `settle-tx.ts`: after each game settlement DB write, check `referral_links` for the settled player(s). If referrer exists, calculate `referrer_earned = fee_lamports * referrer_rate_bps / 10000` and `referee_rebate = fee_lamports * 1000 / 10000` (fixed 10%). Insert into `referral_earnings` in the same DB transaction. Use `getReferrerRate(wallet)` for KOL override (FR-4, FR-10)\n- [ ] [backend] Wrap settlement DB writes in `sql.transaction()` for atomicity — referral earning insert MUST be in the same transaction as the game settlement update (FR-10 + System Invariant 4)\n\n#### Backend — Claim Queue Handler\n- [ ] [backend] Register `referral.claim_requested` handler in queue registry: load claim by ID, verify status is `pending`, update to `processing`, re-verify available balance >= claim amount, execute SOL transfer from server keypair (treasury) to wallet, record tx_signature, update status to `completed`. On failure: record error, update status to `failed`. Idempotent: skip if status is already `completed` (FR-6, FR-11)\n\n#### Frontend — API Client & Plumbing\n- [ ] [frontend] `lib/referral-api.ts` — 7 typed fetch wrappers with JWT Bearer auth following `auth-api.ts` pattern: `generateReferralCode`, `getReferralCode`, `applyReferralCode`, `getReferralStats`, `getReferralEarnings`, `requestReferralClaim`, `pollClaimStatus` (FR-9e)\n- [ ] [frontend] `/r/:code` route in `App.tsx` — capture code to `localStorage` key `referral_code` as `{ code, capturedAt }`, redirect to `/` via `<Navigate replace />` (FR-9a)\n- [ ] [frontend] `useReferralApply` hook — on authentication, if `referral_code` in localStorage and user has no referrer, call `POST /referral/apply`. Clear localStorage on success or permanent failure (invalid/already linked). Keep on transient failure. Show success toast. Mount in `App.tsx` inside auth provider tree (FR-9f)\n\n#### Frontend — Referral Page\n- [ ] [frontend] Sidebar nav item \"Referrals\" in Player section of `Sidebar.tsx` with share/link icon, `--nc: var(--color-green)`, navigates to `/referrals` (FR-9b)\n- [ ] [frontend] `/referrals` route + `ReferralPage` shell: unauthenticated state shows connect-wallet prompt with referral program description. Authenticated state renders feature sections. Wrap in `RouteErrorBoundary` (FR-9c)\n- [ ] [frontend] Referral page §1: \"Your Referral Link\" card — generate code button (if none), display code + full URL + Copy Link button with clipboard feedback. Custom code edit with inline validation (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`) (FR-9c §1)\n- [ ] [frontend] Referral page §2: Stats summary card — four stat boxes (Referred Players, Active 7d, Total Volume, Total Earned) from `GET /referral/stats`. SOL values via lamports→SOL formatting. Loading skeleton (FR-9c §2)\n- [ ] [frontend] Referral page §3: Pending balance card — show unified pending balance prominently. Breakdown: \"From referrals: X SOL\" + \"From fee rebates: Y SOL\". Claim button disabled below threshold, loading during claim, success toast with Solana explorer tx link (FR-9c §3, FR-6)\n- [ ] [frontend] Referral page §4: Earnings history table — paginated from `GET /referral/earnings`. Columns: Date, Game, Referee (truncated wallet), Wager, Your Earning. Empty state message. Pagination controls (FR-9c §4)\n- [ ] [frontend] Profile settings: \"Referral Code\" section in profile settings tab. If no referrer: input + Apply button. If already referred: read-only \"Referred by: [wallet]\". Error states inline (FR-9d)\n\n#### Testing\n- [ ] [test] Backend unit tests for referral routes: code generation, apply (happy path + self-referral + duplicate), stats, earnings pagination, claim flow (happy + zero balance + below threshold + concurrent)\n- [ ] [test] Backend integration test: settle a game for a referred player → verify `referral_earnings` row with correct referrer_earned + referee_rebate amounts\n- [ ] [test] Add local deterministic E2E coverage for primary user flow(s) in `e2e/local/**` (or mark N/A with reason for non-web/non-interactive specs)\n- [ ] [test] Add visual route/state coverage in `e2e/visual/**`; run `pnpm test:visual` and update baselines only for intentional UI changes\n- [ ] [test] Update visual baselines for `/referrals` page (new page) and sidebar (new nav item). Run `pnpm test:visual` to identify failures, then `pnpm test:visual:update` to regenerate. **Before committing**: read old baseline and new screenshot for each changed page (use Read tool on PNG files). Evaluate: **PASS** (changes clearly match spec intent) → commit; **REVIEW** (unexpected areas changed) → save diff images to `docs/specs/300-referral-system/visual-review/`, describe concerns; **FAIL** → fix code\n- [ ] [test] If external provider/oracle/VRF integration is included, add devnet real-provider E2E coverage in `e2e/devnet/**` with env validation + retry/backoff (or mark N/A with reason)\n\n### Testing Requirements\n\nThe agent MUST complete ALL before outputting the completion signal:\n\n#### Code Quality\n- [ ] All existing tests pass\n- [ ] New tests added for new functionality\n- [ ] No lint errors\n\n#### Functional Verification\n- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified\n- [ ] Edge cases handled\n- [ ] Error states handled\n\n#### Visual Regression\n- [ ] `pnpm test:visual` passes (all baselines match)\n- [ ] If this spec changes UI: affected baselines regenerated and committed\n- [ ] Local deterministic E2E passes (`pnpm test:e2e`) for user-facing flows, or N/A documented\n- [ ] Devnet real-provider E2E passes (`pnpm test:e2e:devnet`) when provider-backed flows are included\n\n#### Visual Verification (if UI)\n- [ ] Desktop view correct\n- [ ] Mobile view correct\n\n#### Console/Network Check (if web)\n- [ ] No JS console errors\n- [ ] No failed network requests\n\n#### Smoke Test (Human-in-the-Loop)\n\nBefore declaring done, trace every user-facing flow and verify the experience\nmakes sense from a player's perspective.\n\n- [ ] Generate referral code → copy link → verify URL format\n- [ ] Visit referral link in incognito → authenticate → verify referrer linked\n- [ ] Manually enter code in settings → verify referrer linked\n- [ ] Play a game as referred player → verify referrer earnings appear\n- [ ] Referrer dashboard shows correct stats\n- [ ] Claim earnings → verify SOL arrives in wallet\n- [ ] Attempt self-referral → verify blocked\n- [ ] Attempt to change referrer → verify blocked\n- [ ] Referee fee rebate accrues after playing a game (visible in pending balance)\n- [ ] Referral page shows breakdown: \"From referrals: X\" + \"From fee rebates: Y\"\n\n### Iteration Instructions\n\nIf ANY check fails:\n1. Identify the specific issue\n2. Fix the code\n3. Re-run tests\n4. Re-verify all criteria\n5. Check again\n\n**Only when ALL checks pass, output:** `<promise>DONE</promise>`\n\n### Post-Completion: Gap Analysis\n\nAfter the spec loop outputs `<promise>DONE</promise>`, `spec-loop.sh` automatically runs\n`/gap-analysis {id} --non-interactive` which:\n1. Audits every FR acceptance criterion against the codebase\n2. Writes `docs/specs/{id}/gap-analysis.md` with inventory + audit + recommendations\n3. Annotates FR checkboxes with HTML comment evidence (`<!-- satisfied: ... -->`)\n4. Commits everything together with the completion commit\n","numLines":370,"startLine":348,"totalLines":717}}}
