{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011ANETPz8KPKwBaQu6k2MeU","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Gap Analysis — 301-async-event-queue\n     2→\n     3→**Date**: 2026-03-21\n     4→**Spec Status**: Done\n     5→**Auditor**: Automated (post-completion)\n     6→\n     7→---\n     8→\n     9→## Codebase Inventory\n    10→\n    11→### Migration\n    12→| File | Purpose |\n    13→|------|---------|\n    14→| `services/backend/migrations/010_event_queue.sql` | Table, indexes, CHECK constraint |\n    15→\n    16→### Queue Infrastructure (`services/backend/src/queue/`)\n    17→| File | Purpose |\n    18→|------|---------|\n    19→| `event-types.ts` | `EventTypes` const + `EventType` union |\n    20→| `emit-event.ts` | `emitEvent(tx, type, payload, opts)` producer |\n    21→| `handler-registry.ts` | `registerHandler`, `getHandler`, `clearHandlers` |\n    22→| `worker.ts` | `createEventWorker`, `getBackoffSeconds` |\n    23→| `health.ts` | `getQueueDepth` observability |\n    24→| `index.ts` | Barrel re-exports |\n    25→\n    26→### Backend Wiring\n    27→| File | Lines | Purpose |\n    28→|------|-------|---------|\n    29→| `services/backend/src/config.ts` | 22, 89-92 | `eventQueuePollMs` config (env: `EVENT_QUEUE_POLL_MS`) |\n    30→| `services/backend/src/index.ts` | 24, 172-178 | Import + create + start event worker |\n    31→\n    32→### Tests\n    33→| File | Count | Scope |\n    34→|------|-------|-------|\n    35→| `src/queue/__tests__/queue.test.ts` | 8 tests | emitEvent, handler registry, backoff |\n    36→| `src/queue/__tests__/queue-integration.test.ts` | 3 tests | Happy path, retry→dead, concurrent SKIP LOCKED |\n    37→\n    38→---\n    39→\n    40→## FR Acceptance Criteria Audit\n    41→\n    42→### FR-1: Event Table Schema\n    43→\n    44→| # | Criterion | Verdict | Evidence |\n    45→|---|-----------|---------|----------|\n    46→| 1 | `event_queue` table created via migration | **SATISFIED** | `migrations/010_event_queue.sql:7-22` — CREATE TABLE with all specified columns |\n    47→| 2 | Partial index `(scheduled_at) WHERE status = 'pending'` | **SATISFIED** | `migrations/010_event_queue.sql:25-27` — `idx_event_queue_poll` |\n    48→| 3 | Status index for observability queries | **SATISFIED** | `migrations/010_event_queue.sql:30-31` — `idx_event_queue_status` on `(status, created_at)` |\n    49→| 4 | Status values constrained to: pending, processing, completed, failed, dead | **SATISFIED** | `migrations/010_event_queue.sql:20-21` — `chk_event_queue_status` CHECK constraint |\n    50→\n    51→### FR-2: Event Producer API\n    52→\n    53→| # | Criterion | Verdict | Evidence |\n    54→|---|-----------|---------|----------|\n    55→| 1 | `emitEvent()` inserts within provided transaction | **SATISFIED** | `emit-event.ts:18-34` — accepts `SqlOrTransaction`, uses `tx` template literal |\n    56→| 2 | Committed atomically with triggering operation | **SATISFIED** | `queue.test.ts:76-98` — rollback test proves non-persistence |\n    57→| 3 | Default `max_attempts` = 3, overridable | **SATISFIED** | `emit-event.ts:24` (default 3), `queue.test.ts:100-119` (custom maxAttempts=5) |\n    58→| 4 | `scheduled_at` defaults to now, supports future scheduling | **SATISFIED** | `emit-event.ts:25` (default `new Date()`), `queue.test.ts:100-119` (future Date) |\n    59→| 5 | Returns created event's ID | **SATISFIED** | `emit-event.ts:33` — returns `{ eventId: BigInt(rows[0]!.id) }`, test `queue.test.ts:57-58` |\n    60→\n    61→### FR-3: Event Worker\n    62→\n    63→| # | Criterion | Verdict | Evidence |\n    64→|---|-----------|---------|----------|\n    65→| 1 | Worker loop starts automatically with backend | **SATISFIED** | `index.ts:172-175` — `createEventWorker` + `start()` in backend startup |\n    66→| 2 | Polls every 1-2s, configurable via env | **SATISFIED** | `config.ts:89-92` — `EVENT_QUEUE_POLL_MS` default 1500ms; `worker.ts:44` |\n    67→| 3 | Claims batch ≤10 with `FOR UPDATE SKIP