{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EsZ149HxsCGBH7ihZWCDXq","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile a comprehensive summary document about the DB migration patterns specifically for spec 301 (Async Event Queue).\n\n## Summary: Backend DB Migration Pattern Reference (Spec 301 - Async Event Queue)\n\nBased on my comprehensive read of the project, here's the definitive reference for the DB migration pattern used in spec 301 (Async Event Queue):\n\n### Core Files & Structure\n\n**Migration Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/migrations/010_event_queue.sql`\n\nThe migration system is simple and idempotent:\n- Files are named `NNN_snake_name.sql` (zero-padded sequential: 001, 002, ..., 010)\n- Migrations run automatically on backend startup via `migrate.ts`\n- Tracked in `_migrations` table; applied pending migrations in transactions\n- Support for schema namespacing via `DB_SCHEMA` env var\n\n**Latest Migration (010)** creates a single `event_queue` table with:\n```sql\n- id (BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY) — event ID\n- event_type (TEXT NOT NULL) — event type string\n- payload (JSONB NOT NULL) — event data\n- status (TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending') — current state\n- attempts (INTEGER DEFAULT 0) — retry counter\n- max_attempts (INTEGER DEFAULT 3) — retry limit\n- scheduled_at (TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()) — when to process\n- started_at (TIMESTAMPTZ) — processing start time\n- completed_at (TIMESTAMPTZ) — completion time\n- error (TEXT) — error message on failure\n- created_at (TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()) — insertion timestamp\n\nCHECK constraint: status IN ('pending', 'processing', 'completed', 'failed', 'dead')\nIndex 1: idx_event_queue_poll ON (scheduled_at) WHERE status = 'pending'\nIndex 2: idx_event_queue_status ON (status, created_at)\n```\n\n### Queue Infrastructure Implementation\n\n**Queue Module** (`src/queue/`):\n- `emit-event.ts` — Producer API. Inserts events into the queue within existing DB transactions. Returns `{ eventId: bigint }`. Supports custom `maxAttempts` and `scheduledAt`.\n- `event-types.ts` — Type-safe event constants (`EventTypes.REFERRAL_*`, etc.). Union-exported as `EventType`.\n- `handler-registry.ts` — Maps event type strings to handler functions. Single handler per type. Functions: `registerHandler()`, `getHandler()`, `clearHandlers()`.\n- `worker.ts` — Polling loop that claims events with `FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED`, dispatches to handlers, manages retries with exponential backoff (5s, 30s, 300s+). Supports graceful shutdown.\n- `health.ts` — `getQueueDepth()` returns `{ pending, processing, dead, completed }` counts.\n- `index.ts` — Barrel re-exports all public APIs.\n\n### Usage Pattern\n\n**Emitting events** (from settlement or other hot paths):\n```typescript\nimport { emitEvent } from './queue/index.js';\n\nawait sql.begin(async (tx) => {\n  // Existing settlement logic\n  await settleGame(tx, roundId, outcome);\n  \n  // Emit side-effect event (atomically with settlement)\n  await emitEvent(tx, EventTypes.REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED, {\n    referrerWallet: \"...\",\n    refereeWallet: \"...\",\n    roundId: \"...\",\n    earnedLamports: 12345,\n  }, { \n    maxAttempts: 3,        // Optional: default is 3\n    scheduledAt: new Date() // Optional: default is now\n  });\n  \n  // All committed together, or none if rollback\n});\n```\n\n**Registering handlers** (at backend startup, before worker polling):\n```typescript\nimport { registerHandler, EventTypes } from './queue/index.js';\n\nregisterHandler(EventTypes.REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED, async (payload) => {\n  // Side-effect logic: send SOL, grant rewards, etc.\n  // Must be idempotent — re-processing is a safe no-op\n});\n```\n\n**Starting the worker** (in backend index.ts):\n```typescript\nconst eventWorker = createEventWorker(sql, {\n  pollIntervalMs: 1500,  // Configurable via config.eventQueuePollMs\n  batchSize: 10,         // Default 10 events per poll\n});\neventWorker.start();\neventWorker.stop(); // Graceful shutdown when needed\n```\n\n### Status Lifecycle\n\n```\npending → processing → completed (success)\n                    → pending (retry with backoff if attempts < max_attempts)\n                    → dead (exhausted retries or no handler registered)\n```\n\nAll state transitions are logged with event_id, event_type, and old→new status.\n\n### Key Design Patterns\n\n1. **Atomicity**: Events committed with triggering operation (no orphans, no missed events)\n2. **Concurrency Safety**: `FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED` prevents duplicate processing across multiple workers\n3. **Idempotency**: Handler responsibility to ensure re-processing is safe\n4. **Backoff Strategy**: Exponential (5s attempt 1, 30s attempt 2, 300s attempt 3+), then dead\n5. **Observability**: All transitions logged at appropriate levels (INFO/ERROR/WARN). Dead events marked \"MANUAL REVIEW NEEDED\"\n6. **Extensibility**: New event types + handlers registered without queue infrastructure changes\n\n### Integration Point\n\nBackend startup (`src/index.ts:172-178`):\n```typescript\nconst eventWorker = createEventWorker(sql, {\n  pollIntervalMs: config.eventQueuePollMs,\n});\neventWorker.start();\n```\n\nThe worker runs in-process with settlement worker, clock worker, and PDA watcher.\n\n### Related Files & References\n\n- **Memory Reference**: `/home/vscode/.claude/projects/-workspaces-rng-utopia/memory/reference_db_migrations.md` (outdated; migration 006 listed as latest, now 010)\n- **Spec Document**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/301-async-event-queue/spec.md` (complete with FR-1 through FR-6)\n- **Gap Analysis**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/301-async-event-queue/gap-analysis.md` (acceptance criteria audit, all satisfied)\n- **Tests**: \n  - `src/queue/__tests__/queue.test.ts` (unit: emit, handler registry, backoff)\n  - `src/queue/__tests__/queue-integration.test.ts` (integration: happy path, retry→dead, concurrent SKIP LOCKED)\n\n### What This Pattern Solves\n\nDecouples game settlement (hot path, latency-critical) from side-effects (slower, can fail independently):\n- Reward delivery (send SOL to treasuries)\n- Notifications / emails\n- Analytics / event tracking\n- Achievement evaluation\n- Claim payouts\n\nPlayers see settlement results instantly; side-effects process asynchronously without blocking gameplay."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a47cea458e2944d1a (use SendMessage with to: 'a47cea458e2944d1a' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 56751\ntool_uses: 26\nduration_ms: 117566</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"22eabd0a-3a3b-489d-bc57-d8e8d222d116","uuid":"4337e5ed-b272-4c58-a7b4-3e9bfed9da50","timestamp":"2026-03-24T21:25:39.801Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read the file /home/vscode/.claude/projects/-workspaces-rng-utopia/memory/reference_db_migrations.md to understand the DB migration patterns for this project. Also check if there's an event_queue table migration (related to spec 301) that might be the latest migration.","agentId":"a47cea458e2944d1a","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile a comprehensive summary document about the DB migration patterns specifically for spec 301 (Async Event Queue).\n\n## Summary: Backend DB Migration Pattern Reference (Spec 301 - Async Event Queue)\n\nBased on my comprehensive read of the project, here's the definitive reference for the DB migration pattern used in spec 301 (Async Event Queue):\n\n### Core Files & Structure\n\n**Migration Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/migrations/010_event_queue.sql`\n\nThe migration system is simple and idempotent:\n- Files are named `NNN_snake_name.sql` (zero-padded sequential: 001, 002, ..., 010)\n- Migrations run automatically on backend startup via `migrate.ts`\n- Tracked in `_migrations` table; applied pending migrations in transactions\n- Support for schema namespacing via `DB_SCHEMA` env var\n\n**Latest Migration (010)** creates a single `event_queue` table with:\n```sql\n- id (BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY) — event ID\n- event_type (TEXT NOT NULL) — event type string\n- payload (JSONB NOT NULL) — event data\n- status (TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending') — current state\n- attempts (INTEGER DEFAULT 0) — retry counter\n- max_attempts (INTEGER DEFAULT 3) — retry limit\n- scheduled_at (TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()) — when to process\n- started_at (TIMESTAMPTZ) — processing start time\n- completed_at (TIMESTAMPTZ) — completion time\n- error (TEXT) — error message on failure\n- created_at (TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()) — insertion timestamp\n\nCHECK constraint: status IN ('pending', 'processing', 'completed', 'failed', 'dead')\nIndex 1: idx_event_queue_poll ON (scheduled_at) WHERE status = 'pending'\nIndex 2: idx_event_queue_status ON (status, created_at)\n```\n\n### Queue Infrastructure Implementation\n\n**Queue Module** (`src/queue/`):\n- `emit-event.ts` — Producer API. Inserts events into the queue within existing DB transactions. Returns `{ eventId: bigint }`. Supports custom `maxAttempts` and `scheduledAt`.\n- `event-types.ts` — Type-safe event constants (`EventTypes.REFERRAL_*`, etc.). Union-exported as `EventType`.\n- `handler-registry.ts` — Maps event type strings to handler functions. Single handler per type. Functions: `registerHandler()`, `getHandler()`, `clearHandlers()`.\n- `worker.ts` — Polling loop that claims events with `FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED`, dispatches to handlers, manages retries with exponential backoff (5s, 30s, 300s+). Supports graceful shutdown.\n- `health.ts` — `getQueueDepth()` returns `{ pending, processing, dead, completed }` counts.\n- `index.ts` — Barrel re-exports all public APIs.\n\n### Usage Pattern\n\n**Emitting events** (from settlement or other hot paths):\n```typescript\nimport { emitEvent } from './queue/index.js';\n\nawait sql.begin(async (tx) => {\n  // Existing settlement logic\n  await settleGame(tx, roundId, outcome);\n  \n  // Emit side-effect event (atomically with settlement)\n  await emitEvent(tx, EventTypes.REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED, {\n    referrerWallet: \"...\",\n    refereeWallet: \"...\",\n    roundId: \"...\",\n    earnedLamports: 12345,\n  }, { \n    maxAttempts: 3,        // Optional: default is 3\n    scheduledAt: new Date() // Optional: default is now\n  });\n  \n  // All committed together, or none if rollback\n});\n```\n\n**Registering handlers** (at backend startup, before worker polling):\n```typescript\nimport { registerHandler, EventTypes } from './queue/index.js';\n\nregisterHandler(EventTypes.REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED, async (payload) => {\n  // Side-effect logic: send SOL, grant rewards, etc.\n  // Must be idempotent — re-processing is a safe no-op\n});\n```\n\n**Starting the worker** (in backend index.ts):\n```typescript\nconst eventWorker = createEventWorker(sql, {\n  pollIntervalMs: 1500,  // Configurable via config.eventQueuePollMs\n  batchSize: 10,         // Default 10 events per poll\n});\neventWorker.start();\neventWorker.stop(); // Graceful shutdown when needed\n```\n\n### Status Lifecycle\n\n```\npending → processing → completed (success)\n                    → pending (retry with backoff if attempts < max_attempts)\n                    → dead (exhausted retries or no handler registered)\n```\n\nAll state transitions are logged with event_id, event_type, and old→new status.\n\n### Key Design Patterns\n\n1. **Atomicity**: Events committed with triggering operation (no orphans, no missed events)\n2. **Concurrency Safety**: `FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED` prevents duplicate processing across multiple workers\n3. **Idempotency**: Handler responsibility to ensure re-processing is safe\n4. **Backoff Strategy**: Exponential (5s attempt 1, 30s attempt 2, 300s attempt 3+), then dead\n5. **Observability**: All transitions logged at appropriate levels (INFO/ERROR/WARN). Dead events marked \"MANUAL REVIEW NEEDED\"\n6. **Extensibility**: New event types + handlers registered without queue infrastructure changes\n\n### Integration Point\n\nBackend startup (`src/index.ts:172-178`):\n```typescript\nconst eventWorker = createEventWorker(sql, {\n  pollIntervalMs: config.eventQueuePollMs,\n});\neventWorker.start();\n```\n\nThe worker runs in-process with settlement worker, clock worker, and PDA watcher.\n\n### Related Files & References\n\n- **Memory Reference**: `/home/vscode/.claude/projects/-workspaces-rng-utopia/memory/reference_db_migrations.md` (outdated; migration 006 listed as latest, now 010)\n- **Spec Document**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/301-async-event-queue/spec.md` (complete with FR-1 through FR-6)\n- **Gap Analysis**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/301-async-event-queue/gap-analysis.md` (acceptance criteria audit, all satisfied)\n- **Tests**: \n  - `src/queue/__tests__/queue.test.ts` (unit: emit, handler registry, backoff)\n  - `src/queue/__tests__/queue-integration.test.ts` (integration: happy path, retry→dead, concurrent SKIP LOCKED)\n\n### What This Pattern Solves\n\nDecouples game settlement (hot path, latency-critical) from side-effects (slower, can fail independently):\n- Reward delivery (send SOL to treasuries)\n- Notifications / emails\n- Analytics / event tracking\n- Achievement evaluation\n- Claim payouts\n\nPlayers see settlement results instantly; side-effects process asynchronously without blocking gameplay."}],"totalDurationMs":117566,"totalTokens":56751,"totalToolUseCount":26,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6119,"cache_read_input_tokens":48886,"output_tokens":1746,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6119},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
